    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen using `bdelete` to delete some buffers, the nvim may give some errors related to the LSPs\n\n```\n îª‡  Error  07:48:18 PM msg_show.lua_error\n\nError executing vim.schedule lua callback: /usr/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/uri.lua:83: Invalid buffer id: 11\nstack traceback:\n\t[C]: in function 'nvim_buf_get_name'\n\t/usr/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/uri.lua:83: in function 'uri_from_bufnr'\n\t/usr/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/util.lua:205: in function 'get_lines'\n\t/usr/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/util.lua:268: in function 'get_line'\n\t/usr/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/util.lua:282: in function 'get_line_byte_from_position'\n\t/usr/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/util.lua:1685: in function 'buf_highlight_references'\n\t/usr/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/handlers.lua:467: in function 'handler'\n\t/usr/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/client.lua:681: in function ''\n\tvim/_editor.lua: in function <vim/_editor.lua:0>\n```\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Use nvim to open one file to which at least one LSP will attach\n2. Before the LSP's ready, use `:bdelete` to delete the buffer\n3. Wait for the LSP be ready, and nvim will give an error that trying to update one invalid buffer\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nWhen the buffer is not valid again, LSP should do nothing for the buffer.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.11.2\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nIDK\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArch Linux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nWezTerm\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\ntmux-256color\n\n### Installation\n\ninstalled from pacman",
